                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.937/23: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-07-01T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 1, 1929—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>221. Your 515, June 27, 11 a.m. Department believes that it would be well to
                    instruct Consul General at Hankow, if he considers such action advisable, to
                    take up matter with local authorities and attempt <pb facs="0957" n="813"
                        xml:id="pg_813"/> to effect local settlement. In the meantime company may
                    consider it desirable to prepare formal diplomatic claim as suggested in your
                    instruction of April 22 to Hankow. Report developments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
